Second, unemployment is still more prevalent among youth than among other age groups. Particularly 
youth without upper secondary education face considerable difficulties in finding employment (Figure 10, 
panel B). One possible reason is the high minimum wage which might hurt the young disproportionately as 
they tend to be less productive than other workers due to the lack of experience. Figure 10. The labour market situation of young adults Per cent 1. 
